sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I750009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part uses the cI inverter to stimulate an output in response to red light.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Patricia Illing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I750006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is constructed from existing registry parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part inverts the activating output of OmpR so that transcription of a desired coding sequence can be triggered in the response to reduced EnvZ activity. The endogenous protein OmpR is phosphorylated by EnvZ. Phosphorylated OmpR then binds its response element (BBa_R0084) activating transcription. By placing the cI inverter system (BBa_Q04510) behind this promotor transcription of a desired product can be triggered by reduced EnvZ activity. This part is intended to invert the activating output of the red light receptor system BBa_M30109 in the absense of light to a repression of transcription. As a result transcription should be activated in the presence of red light.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Patricia Illing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M30109
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Pbad regulated phycobilins (ho1 and pcyA) followed by Ptet regulated light sensor (Cph8). This should allow repressed Pbad to give low levels of accessory proteins and derepressed Ptet to crank out lots of light sensor protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: natalie kuldell

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_Q04510
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lambda cI QPI w/ strong RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy and Jennifer Braff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompF. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter includes three OmpR binding sites: F1, F2, and F3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1. A distant fourth binding site, F4, has been deleted. It is involved in negative regulation of ompF (Head, Tardy and Kenney, 1998), so its deletion is intended to make the promoter solely activating. The efficacy of this promoter versus the ompC upstream region (BBa_R0082) or the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) is currently unknown.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I15008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: One of two requisite genes required for the biosynthesis of phycocyanobilin from heme.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Tabor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13453
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PBad promoter from I0500 without AraC.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I15009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Second of two required phycocyanobilin biosynthetic genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Tabor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I15010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Silent mutation at base 108 (G-A) to remove PstI site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Tabor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
